==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apo
<hw>Ap"o</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <?/. See <er>Ab-</er>.]</ety>
<def>A prefix from a Greek preposition. It usually signifies
<xex>from</xex>, <xex>away from</xex>, <xex>off</xex>, or
<xex>asunder</xex>, <xex>separate</xex>; <as>as, in <ex>apo</ex>cope (a
cutting <ex>off</ex>), <ex>apo</ex>state, <ex>apo</ex>stle (one sent
<ex>away</ex>), <ex>apo</ex>carpous</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>


<p><ent>Apocalypse</ent>⟦br⟧
